title: 820-000165 no power
message:
So this was originally water damaged macbook air. changed u7100 and put it though ultrasonic cleaner. afterward computer was working fine, and passed asd. It sat in my shop for 89 days (i only hold them for 90). Went to show customer and now does power up.


Orarge light
no fan spin
pp3v42 - 3.42
ppbus - 8.58
pp3v3_s0 - 0
pp3v3_s5 - 0

what line is the the vcore?

title: 820-000165 no power
message: If you don’t have S5 rails you won’t have VCore. What is the resistance to ground on 3v3_S5? Is PPVRTC_G3H present?

title: 820-000165 no power
message:
I don't know what that means. 2.828 what?

Is SMC_PM_G2_EN present? What voltage?

title: 820-000165 no power
message: If you mean 2.82 volts then that would at least indicate a problem around U1900 and the clock circuit as it needs to be 3.3. Also yes as Louis asked is G2 EN present?

title: 820-000165 no power
message:
okay replaced u1900 now have 3.322v
SMC_PM_G2_EN - 3.420v

Edit: have fan spin now (its on max) but no chime.

I'm not sure if this is vcore but

PPVCC_S0_CPU_PH1 - is 1.808

title: 820-000165 no power
message: Brain dead, could be water damage around U6100, J6100, SMC...

title: 820-000165 no power
message: no corrsion on j6100.  should i replace u6100 or smc first?

title: 820-000165 no power
message: Don't touch the SMC yet!! Kill JTAGs as your heart desires..

title: 820-000165 no power
message: Check termination resistors and traces from U6100 to CPU and SMC. Also suspect would be crap under the SMC. It all depends on where the original corrosion damage was.
